Predictive Modelling on Big Mart Sales Data¶

This piece of code includes a full machine learning project including the whole pipeline of operations outlined below:¶

  1. data preparation
  2. data cleaning
  3. choosing models
  4. training a model
  5. evaluating the model
  6. make predictions

The packages used in this programming are: Pandas, Numpy, Scikit-Learn

The 'Big Mart Predictive Sales Report' accompanies this code and demonstrates understanding of ethical design.

Data Cleaning¶

Both test and train are cleaned because the test set reflects the system's performance against real-time data, you need to perform a clean-up of the data in the test set.

The only difference between the two sets are:

  • the size
  • the sales column in test is empty

Data Cleaning Plan¶

  • Keeping all columns of data, do not need any data column drops - df.drop()
  • Changed column names to: Item_Id & Outlet_Id
  • Standardise/ clean the content within the columns
  • Check value counts to see what needs to be adjusted - value.counts()
  • Replace all missing data points with mean for Item_Weight
  • Replace all missing data points with median for Outlet_Size

Example of Changes -

  • Item_Weight - empty points to N/A
  • Item_Fat_Content - LF, Low Fat, low fat to Low; Reg to Regular
In [7]:
# Cleaning column names 

def clean_col(col):
    col = col.strip()
    col = col.replace("Item_Identifier", "Item_Id")
    col = col.replace("Outlet_Identifier", "Outlet_Id")
    col = col.replace(" ","_")
    col = col.title()
    return col

new_columns = []
for c in df.columns:
    clean_c = clean_col(c)
    new_columns.append(clean_c)
    
df.columns = new_columns

Changing columns¶

  1. New column New_Item_Type represents, Food, Drink or Non-Consumables, using the first two letters of Item_Id
  2. Item_visib_avg will show the mean visibility given to the same product in all other stores.

#Changing only the first 2 characters (i.e. the category ID)

df['New_Item_Type'] = df['Item_Id'].apply(lambda x: x[0:2])

Item Visibility¶

  • visibility is very right skewed, majority of the values are low.
  • most items we buy in a supermarket are essentials so either don't require 'good visibility' as they are ingreidients that customers solely go into a shop for.
  • meat and dairy are considered as essentials and they are kept in a fridge, typically located at the back of the shop.

Outlet Establishment¶

  • shows that the most previous outlet was established in 2009.

Item Outlet Sales¶

  • right skewed again
  • majority are between 0 and 7000

One Hot Encoding Categorical Variables¶

One hot encoding makes our training data more useful and expressive, and it can be rescaled easily. By using numeric values, we more easily determine a probability for our values. In particular, one hot encoding is used for our output values, since it provides more nuanced predictions than single labels.

https://www.google.com/search?q=purpose+of+one+hot+encoding&oq=purpose+of+one+hot+encoding&aqs=chrome..69i57j0i22i30l3j0i390l3.4760j1j7&sourceid=chrome&ie=UTF-8

Fitting Models¶

Linear Regression¶

THIS IS NOT A CLASSIFIACTION PROBLEM

Linear regression is the next step up after correlation. It is used when we want to predict the value of a variable based on the value of another variable. The variable we want to predict is called the dependent variable (or sometimes, the outcome variable).
